## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="6cc2e-149">O <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider.BuildSiteMap%2A> método é chamado para carregar e compilar o mapa do site do armazenamento persistente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6cc2e-149">The <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider.BuildSiteMap%2A> method is called to load and build the site map from persistent storage.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="6cc2e-150">Para o comportamento padrão quando a restrição de segurança está habilitada, consulte "Comentários" em <xref:System.Web.SiteMapProvider.IsAccessibleToUser%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6cc2e-150">For the default behavior when security trimming is enabled, see "Remarks" in <xref:System.Web.SiteMapProvider.IsAccessibleToUser%2A>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="6cc2e-151">Após o <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> objeto analisa e carrega os dados de mapa de site, todos carregados <xref:System.Web.SiteMapNode> objetos e <xref:System.Web.SiteMapNodeCollection> coleções são somente leitura.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6cc2e-151">After the <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> object parses and loads site map data, all loaded <xref:System.Web.SiteMapNode> objects and <xref:System.Web.SiteMapNodeCollection> collections are made read-only.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="6cc2e-152">Quando o <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> analisa o <xref:System.Web.SiteMapNode.Url%2A> propriedade de um arquivo de mapa de site, ele converte URLs relativas de aplicativos, bem como URLs relativas, para caminhos virtuais absoluto do aplicativo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6cc2e-152">When the <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> parses the <xref:System.Web.SiteMapNode.Url%2A> property from a site map file, it converts application-relative URLs, as well as relative URLs, to application-absolute virtual paths.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="6cc2e-153">O <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> se inscreve para notificações de alteração de arquivo para o arquivo de sitemap.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6cc2e-153">The <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> subscribes to file change notifications for the .sitemap file.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="6cc2e-154">Se qualquer alteração for feita para o arquivo de sitemap, o <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> é recarregado, e a estrutura de mapa do site será reconstruída.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6cc2e-154">If any change is made to the .sitemap file, the <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> is reloaded, and the site map structure is rebuilt.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="6cc2e-155">O exemplo de código a seguir demonstra como criar uma nova instância do <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> classe e inicializá-lo para criar um mapa de site dos dados XML.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6cc2e-155">The following code example demonstrates how to create a new instance of the <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> class and initialize it to build a site map from XML data.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
<%@ Page Language="c#" %>  
 <!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN">  
 <SCRIPT runat="server">  
 private void Page_Load(object sender, System.EventArgs e)  
 {  
     // Create an instance of the XmlSiteMapProvider class.  
     XmlSiteMapProvider testXmlProvider = new XmlSiteMapProvider();  
     NameValueCollection providerAttributes = new NameValueCollection(1);  
     providerAttributes.Add("siteMapFile","test.sitemap");  
     // Initialize the provider with a provider name and file name.  
     testXmlProvider.Initialize("testProvider", providerAttributes);  
  
     // The BuildSiteMap method is implicitly called when the   
     // RootNode propety is accessed.  
  
     // Prints "/myvirtualdirectory/WebForm1.aspx"  
     Response.Write(testXmlProvider.RootNode.Url + "<BR>");  
     // Prints "/myvirtualdirectory/WebForm2.aspx"  
     Response.Write(testXmlProvider.CurrentNode.Url + "<BR>");  
 }  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="6cc2e-156">O exemplo de código anterior usa um arquivo XML que está localizado na raiz virtual do aplicativo ASP.NET.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6cc2e-156">The preceding code example uses an XML file that is located in the virtual root of the ASP.NET application.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="6cc2e-157">O arquivo tem o seguinte formato:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6cc2e-157">The file has the following format:</span></span>  
  
```  
<siteMap>  
     <siteMapNode title="RootNode" description="The root page." url="WebForm1.aspx">  
         <siteMapNode title="CurrentNode" description="Some sub page." url="WebForm2.aspx"/>  
     </siteMapNode>  
 </siteMap>  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="6cc2e-245">O <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> classe substitui o herdadas <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider.Initialize%2A> método para aplicar vários atributos, como o `siteMapFile` e `description` atributos, como o `attributes` coleção.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6cc2e-245">The <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> class overrides the inherited <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider.Initialize%2A> method to apply several attributes, such as the `siteMapFile` and `description` attributes, to the `attributes` collection.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="6cc2e-246">O exemplo de código a seguir demonstra como criar uma nova instância do <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> classe e inicializá-lo para criar um mapa de site dos dados XML.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6cc2e-246">The following code example demonstrates how to create a new instance of the <xref:System.Web.XmlSiteMapProvider> class and initialize it to build a site map from XML data.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
<%@ Page Language="c#" %>  
<SCRIPT runat="server">  
 private void Page_Load(object sender, System.EventArgs e) {  
     // Create an instance of the XmlSiteMapProvider class.  
     XmlSiteMapProvider testXmlProvider = new XmlSiteMapProvider();  
     NameValueCollection providerAttributes = new NameValueCollection(1);  
     providerAttributes.Add("siteMapFile","test.sitemap");  
  
     // Initialize the provider with a provider name and file name.  
     testXmlProvider.Initialize("testProvider", providerAttributes);  
  
     // Call the BuildSiteMap to load the site map information into memory.  
     testXmlProvider.BuildSiteMap();  
  
     // Prints "/myvirtualdirectory/WebForm1.aspx"  
     Response.Write(testXmlProvider.RootNode.Url + "<BR>");  
  
     // Prints "/myvirtualdirectory/WebForm2.aspx"  
     Response.Write(testXmlProvider.CurrentNode.Url + "<BR>");  
 }  
 </SCRIPT>  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="6cc2e-247">O exemplo de código anterior usa um arquivo XML que está localizado na raiz virtual do aplicativo ASP.NET.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6cc2e-247">The preceding code example uses an XML file that is located in the virtual root of the ASP.NET application.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="6cc2e-248">O arquivo tem o seguinte formato:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6cc2e-248">The file has the following format:</span></span>  
  
```  
<siteMap>  
  <siteMapNode title="RootNode" description="The root page." url="WebForm1.aspx">  
    <siteMapNode title="CurrentNode" description="Some sub page." url="WebForm2.aspx"/>  
  </siteMapNode>  
</siteMap>  
```
